    <text>
        <body>
            <pb n="1"/>
            <p>
                <addressee>Mr Isaac Leeser</addressee>
            </p>
            <p rend="indent(1)">
                <placeName>Philadelphia</placeName>
            </p>
            <p rend="align(right)"><placeName>Curacao</placeName>
                <date>Novr 26<hi rend="sup">th</hi> 1866</date>.</p>
            <p>Dear Sir.</p>
            <p rend="indent(1)">I am possession of your of the <date><sic>3th</sic>
                August</date><lb/> ulto. contents of it duly noted, I return to you hereby the
                pro-<lb/>spectus list with the names of some friends on it as sub-<lb/>scribers, I
                am sorry I could not <sic>obtained</sic> some more up to<lb/> this, but not to keep
                it longer by me I do so, however I<lb/> will try always to get some of our people of
                    <placeName>Nueva Gra-<lb/>nada</placeName> &amp; of
                    <placeName>Venezuela</placeName> when they come here, I have not pre-<lb/>sented
                to any of the reform people on acct the hate and<lb/> the <sic>deslike</sic> which
                they have for Judaism and being these <sic>reli-<lb/>geous</sic> works I supposed
                they should have refused to sign it<lb/> their reform I assure you is not like of
                the others congregation,<lb/> they revenge their capricious with religion matter by
                aboli-<lb/>shing on every occasion the precepts of our Law, as on the last<lb/>
                <date>Rosh a shana</date> no <hi rend="underline">sophar</hi> at all, <date>Kipur
                    day</date>
                <persName>Mr. Henriques<lb/> M. D.</persName> delivered a discourse in which saying
                to his people<lb/> that by fasting two hours that day it is quite sufficient
                and<lb/> his good <sic>advise</sic> made that nearly all the congregation have<lb/>
                done so, among them selves many do not like such reform,<lb/> but the chiefs ones
                    <sic>geveeng</sic> always for <sic>reasen</sic> that the reform<lb/> of
                    <placeName>New York</placeName> it is so, as the Tefelim, Tales<add>?</add>,
                Sophar, Lulab<add>?</add> riding<lb/> of the carriage and <sic>smocking</sic> on
                        <date><sic>Saterday</sic></date>, on cover in the<lb/>
                <sic>Sinagogue</sic>, no celebration of <date>Purim</date> or
                        <date><sic>Hannica</sic></date> no prayers at the<lb/> circumcision &amp;
                many <sic>others</sic> ceremonies which they have<lb/>
                <sic>aboleshed</sic></p>
            <pb n="2"/>
            <p><sic>intirly</sic> and calling that Progress, I wish to know from<lb/> you if it is
                so or not in the Emannuel Temple of <placeName>New York</placeName><lb/> that I may
                in case if it is not to contradict them. They<lb/> are standing with same number of
                members as for last<lb/> 18 months. - For the present I conclude with the hope
                to<lb/> write you soon again, and remaining</p>
            <p rend="indent(2)">Your Obdt Servt</p>
            <p rend="indent(2)">
                <persName role="author">B de Casseres</persName>
            </p>
            <pb n="3"/>
            <p>
                <addressee>Isaac Leeser Esqr.</addressee>
            </p>
            <p rend="indent(1)"><placeName>1227 Walnut Street</placeName>.</p>
            <p rend="indent(2)"><placeName>Philadelphia</placeName>.</p>
